{"title": "After Quad, a Quint for the Arctic", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2022-02-03", "content": "Just over two months ago, the world narrowly escaped an ecological disaster in the Arctic.\nTwo Russian oil barges transporting diesel oil and paraffin to the remote Arctic region went aground off the north-western tip of Vaygach island, a spot in the Arctic Ocean that is between the seas of Pechora and Kara."}